The paper discusses a technique for optimizing GPU memory accesses for drawing from discrete distributions, which is a common task in machine learning and data analysis. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to these fields, such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Among these, cs.DC and cs.DS seem particularly relevant as they deal with efficient computation and data management, while cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CV are also possible as they involve machine learning and data analysis.
